The paper discusses network pruning, which is a common technique used in deep learning for reducing the inference cost of models. This technique is widely used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and other areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the training and fine-tuning of models, which are core topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL, in that order.
